data.meta_description: A Community Clinic for Psychological Services
data.text:
About the Gronowski Center

The Gronowski Center is a community mental health clinic associated with Palo Alto University. The Center was established in 1988 by Kurt and Barbara Gronowski to provide low-cost, evidence-based psychological services for the underserved within our community.Over 30 years later, the Gronowski Center holds true to this vision and remains committed to the psychological well-being of our communityâ€™s residents.

The Gronowski Center is dedicated to providing counseling and psychotherapy services to adults, children, adolescents, older adults, couples, and families.
